																		Re: The Reality Dreamer
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5336470&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204973" alt="cybersqyd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5336470)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;" >cybersqyd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1610089904 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Jan 2021 07:11</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4864887">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Overall</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Overall</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I don't hate this; and I think a lot of it's a fine start; but it feels&#8230;narratively lacking?</p>
<p>You said your main concern is the dialogue: beyond a few places where I've highlighted the flow of the conversation is weird, the actual like individual lines of dialogue and characters are all fine.</p>
<p>Indeed, generally the writing quality here is pretty alright.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, the big issue for me is there's not really a big hook: you theoretically have this interplay between the SCP being &quot;dangerous&quot; and the SCP being actually very friendly; where like, you have the containment logs indicating how big and dangerous this SCP is, contrasted with the relatively scared feeling in the first interview and the friendliness of the second. This doesn't land though: there's never a feeling of the SCP's effects actually having consequences; you mention things like 'the possibility that all individuals within the area have been affected' and 'the researcher was automatically woken after SCP-XXXX's range had breached thirty kilometers' but there's no grounding in this: we never see what effect the huge range or every individual in an area being affected actually has on the people, so the 'danger' of this is never established and the threat doesn't feel real.</p>
<p>Technically the hook could be the growth of the SCP: them like, becoming used to the situation and like, growing to harness their power better; but the problem is that it never feels like this is really <em>shown</em>. Like, the SCP definitely feels like they change a lot between the first and second interviews and it's not bad that this change happens, but it is bad that it's not shown to the reader.</p>
<p>I think the Containment Updates in the middle kinda makes this awkward for you. They're very detached from the consequences cos they're focussed on the containment; which makes conveying the scope of the danger hard with them; but they're also very focussed on what the Foundation is doing which makes conveying why the Foundation is doing stuff hard too; and so it doesn't really convey a sense of tension?</p>
<p>I feel like I have been quite harsh here: I like a lot of what this does conceptually, and I like the core of the story you're trying to tell here; I just don't think you've effectively told that story.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Overall</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><em>Gonna note that I can miss stuff; flag things which are right as being wrong and indeed flag things which are deliberately wrong.</em><br />
<em>I'll likely use <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">strikethrough</span> to indicate stuff to remove and <span style="color: green">green text</span> to indicate stuff to add.</em></p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX must be kept at least thirty meters away from any humans or other members of the Hominidae family undergoing R.E.M. sleep while it is sufficiently contained by means of SCP-XXXX-01A.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This feels&#8230;overlong as a sentence? The part about 01A feels iffy like if it's sufficiently contained, why does it need to be 30m from other folk undergoing R.E.M. sleep? It seems like it's meant to be a separate thing?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX's chamber is to be outfitted with a functioning nasogastric feeding tube and catheter.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would probably refer to what the chamber is at least roughly somewhere before this (e.g. in the first sentence, using '&#8230;must be kept in a humanoid containment chamber at least&#8230;' say)</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Any non-essential personnel of at least Level-2 security clearance are permitted to sleep within SCP-XXXX's range between the hours of 22:00 and 08:00 (subject to anomaly's discretion.)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Earlier you say it must be kept away from any humans in REM sleep: either non-essential personnel are allowed to sleep near it or that; you can't have both.</p>
<p>I'm a little hesitant at 'subject to anomaly's discretion' here too; it feels a little too much like the anomaly is being allowed to treat the foundation containment like a hotel?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is a white male of advanced age.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'advanced age' feels a little vague to me</p>
<blockquote>
<p>functions inside a void-like sub-reality referred to as SCP-XXXX-01.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd probably use 'SCP-XXXX-1' here just to cut down a digit; and 'void-like' feels a little weirdly vague</p>
<blockquote>
<p>within its range enters into the rapid eye movement stage of sleep.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>you don't actually specify what this range is: the implication is 30m from the ConProcs but realistically there should be a margin of error on that (e.g., if the SCP's range is 10m, you want people 20m away just in case something happens and the range is bigger than expected or centred differently than expected)</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-01A has been forcibly enlisted to counteract the properties of SCP-XXXX's body by improving the anomaly's overall mood and decreasing its influence.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>you don't actually say what -01A is here and it feels&#8230;weird.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Document XXXX-01 is an official Foundation record, any unauthorized examination is punishable by termination.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd increase the size of this a touch; it's real tiny on my screen and almost a little hard to read.</p>
<p>I'm also not a fan of 'examination' here; it feels like 'access' might be better? Though termination feels harsh here too</p>
<blockquote>
<p>What are you people doing here? Going in and out, get me out, please.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This feels, a little too all over the place? I think the second sentence needs just, a few more words to flesh out the ideas the SCP is trying to convey?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX: I said let me speak.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The last thing the scp said was 'I want to talk, let's talk, I'll talk'; and it kinda feels a little too much like it means &quot;I'll answer your questions then&quot; in meaning for this to not feel a little jarring?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I require your full cooperation to make that come to <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">past</span><span style="color: green">pass</span>.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Yes, well, several hundred people were trapped in here with you before we could get your physical form out of the city.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The 'Yes, well,' feels&#8230;out of place here? I can't quite put my finger on why but I think it's because the SCP hasn't like&#8230;asked a question or whatever.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Containment Update 20/11/15:</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It feels weird to jump chronologically back to before the interview here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>at the possibility of training Type Greens.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'Type Green' is GOC lingo and generally not what the Foundation calls 'em</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
</div>
</div>

